      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DARK MOONSHINE (3) was well fancied last time on the strength of a win two back but could only manage fifth (20.34) at this track. Better than the latest run and deserves another chance. REV LEON (5) has a fair record and proved too classy last time to win by 0.8 lengths at this track in a handy 19.96 beating Long Gully Ash. Goes well out of this box with a win and four minor placings. Can make it two on the bounce. SPLIT VISION (7) hit the ground running last start and was never headed (19.68) at this track in Other over 342m. Winner at his latest appearance in one of the quickest times on the card. Sure to be thereabouts. SLIPPER'S MAGGIE (1) cannot be written off despite a miss here at her latest outing.",
